content:
The Service Setup Assistant walks you through essential setup tasks to get Service Cloud up and running. After a few clicks, your team can start using key Service Cloud features that are configured with optimal settings and layouts.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To set up the Service Setup Assistant, you need:

* Customize Application
* Service Cloud User

Core Tasks:
1. Create a custom Lightning Service Console.
2. Create Email-to-Case queue and configure Email-to-Case settings.
3. Set up Omni-Channel and configure case routing.
4. Enable Messaging & Messaging routing.
5. Create Case and Messaging permission sets.
6. Create Case Status picklist values.
7. Enable Case Merge.
8. Set up automatic email notifications for case updates.

Some features require extra licenses or configuration steps:
* Knowledge requires a Knowledge license.
* Case routing requires a Service Cloud license or Digital Engagement license.
* Messaging requires a Digital Engagement license.
* Macros requires a Service Cloud license.

Users must be assigned a feature-specific license and permission set to access Knowledge, Case, and Messaging.
title: Service Setup Assistant in Salesforce
